THE country’s anti-corruption agency has bust a landlord and his 10 tenants. This was during a crackdown that led to the arrest of 20 suspected internet fraudsters. The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission arrested landlord Stanley Ejike Awam (33) in Ibadan, the capital city of Oyo State. The commission’s acting spokesman said: “Awam was apprehended for allegedly providing shelter for the suspected internet fraudsters.” The suspects were arrested in the premises of the six-flat bungalow. Items recovered from them include three exotic cars, laptops, mobile phones and land documents. The commission also arrested another 10 suspected online fraudsters during a sting operation in Lagos. – CAJ NEWS